# Vendored third-party browser assets, fetched on demand — NOT committed.
#
# The Mermaid UMD bundle (mermaid.min.js) is MIT, but it inlines elkjs
# (EPL-2.0, weak copyleft) and others, and redistributing a minified blob
# carries attribution duties. Keeping it out of the repo preserves this
# framework's MIT/permissive-only, copyleft-free policy. Obtain it locally:
#
#   cd skills/garelier-core/driver && bun run vendor:mermaid
#
# At runtime the status server serves it from here (no CDN). Without it, the
# console shows ```mermaid blocks as readable source.
*
!.gitignore
!README.md
